creatorWithdraw(address,uint256).details: This function is callable only after cycle expiry if goal is met.

params.receivingAddress: Contract Owner must call this function, but they can input another address to receive funds if desired.

depositRefundBonus(uint256).details: Can only be called by the contract owner / project creator.

didPay((address,uint256,uint256,(address.details: Reverts if the calling contract is not one of the project's terminals.This example implementation reverts if the payer isn't on the allow list.

params._data: Standard Juicebox project payment data. See https://docs.juicebox.money/dev/api/data-structures/jbdidpaydata/.

params._projectId: The ID of the project this contract's functionality applies to.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

payParams((address,address,(address,uint.details: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource.This implementation just sets this contract up to receive a `didPay` call.

params._data: The Juicebox standard project payment data. See https://docs.juicebox.money/dev/api/data-structures/jbpayparamsdata/.

returns.delegateAllocations: Amount to be sent to delegates instead of adding to local balance. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as payment come in.
returns.memo: A memo to be forwarded to the event. Useful for describing any new actions that are being taken.
returns.weight: The weight that project tokens should get minted relative to. This is useful for optionally customizing how many tokens are issued per payment.

params._data: Standard Juicebox project redemption data. See https://docs.juicebox.money/dev/api/data-structures/jbredeemparamsdata/.

returns.delegateAllocations: Amount to be sent to delegates instead of being added to the beneficiary. Useful for auto-routing funds from a treasury as redemptions are sought.
returns.memo: A memo to be forwarded to the event. Useful for describing any new actions are being taken.
returns.reclaimAmount: Amount to be reclaimed from the treasury. This is useful for optionally customizing how much funds from the treasury are disbursed per redemption.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._interfaceId: The ID of the interface to check for adherence to.

returns._0: A flag indicating if the provided interface ID is supported.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

depositRefundBonus(uint256).notice: Refund bonus is deposited before funding cycle start to increase potential pledger confidence.

didPay((address,uint256,uint256,(address.notice: Received hook from the payment terminal after a payment.

didRedeem((address,uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: If cycle meets project target, then this function cannot be called, since pauseRedemptions will be on. If cycle fails to meet target, then this function will proceed all the way through for early pledgers.

initialize(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint3.notice: Initializes the Dominant Assurance part of this contract with project details and a directory from which ecosystem payment terminals and controller can be found. Function should be called prior to funding cycle start.

payParams((address,address,(address,uint.notice: This function gets called when the project receives a payment.

redeemParams((address,address,uint256,ui.notice: This function gets called when the project's token holders redeem.

relayCycleResults().notice: After the funding cycle ends, anyone can call this function to store the cycle results.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Indicates if this contract adheres to the specified interface.
